# Trivy vulnerability allow-list for the CD image scan (cd.yml).
#
# Parity with pip-audit in .github/workflows/ci.yml: the gate still fails on
# every NEW or FIXABLE CVE — only the documented advisories below, which cannot
# be cleared by a runtime dependency pin, are suppressed.
#
# The former urllib3 block (CVE-2025-50181 / CVE-2025-66418 / CVE-2025-66471 /
# CVE-2026-21441 / CVE-2026-44431) was REMOVED: the kubernetes 28->31 bump lifted
# the old urllib3 <2.0.0 cap, so urllib3 is now 2.x where all five are fixed
# (verified clean by pip-audit). No urllib3 exceptions remain.
#
# wheel / jaraco.context — build/packaging tooling pre-installed in the base
# python image (and not removable by a requirements pin under pip
# --no-index). Both advisories require an attacker-supplied malicious wheel or
# tar at BUILD time — outside the runtime threat model of the deployed image
# (no build/packaging happens in the running container). Tracked for cleanup
# via a base-image tooling refresh.
#   wheel          CVE-2026-24049 — priv-esc via malicious wheel (fix 0.46.2)
#   jaraco.context CVE-2026-23949 — path traversal via malicious tar (fix 6.1.0)
CVE-2026-24049
CVE-2026-23949
